c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Gemini is best suited for Google workspace users, multimodal tasks, research, coding, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Inflection, meanwhile, shines for enterprise, custom AI assistants, business workflows, productivity, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Gemini describes itself as \"Google's multimodal AI chatbot with deep Google integration.\" Inflection, established in 2022, positions itself as \"Enterprise AI platform by the creators of Pi.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Gemini** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 4), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Inflection is a poor choice — far from it. Inflection excels in its own right, particularly for enterprise and custom AI assistants.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep integration with google services, go with Gemini. If enterprise-grade security and reliability matters more to you, Inflection is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
